4. Verification of the Feigenbaum Alpha
The scaling constant alpha measures how the bifurcation splitting near the critical point x = 0.5 shrinks at each period-doubling. At the superstable r_n, the second-nearest orbit point to x = 0.5 gives the splitting distance d_n. The ratio d_n / d_{n+1} estimates alpha.
def alpha_estimate(n):
   r_n, r_np1 = superstable_r(n), superstable_r(n+1)
   for r, nd in [(r_n, n), (r_np1, n+1)]:
       orb = orbit_at_superstable(r, nd)
       dists = abs(orb - 0.5)
       d = min(dists[dists > 1e-10])
   return d_n / d_{n+1}
 
 
